Yan Diomande ‘confirmed’ as Liverpool target but €100m price tag “excessive”
March 27, 2026
•
Jack Lusby
Liverpool are widely credited with an interest in RB Leipzig winger Yan Diomande but any plans to sign him as Mo Salah‘s replacement are stunted by his price tag.

With Salah now confirmed to be departing Anfield on a free transfer this summer, Liverpool are ramping up their efforts to sign a new wide player.

The expectation is that this cannot be a like-for-like replacement, as despite his decline this season Salah is still viewed as one of the best in the world in his position.

Instead Liverpool could return their model of banking on potential, with Leipzig youngster Diomande, 19, confirmed as a player of interest.

