The Athletic‘s James Pearce has joined high-profile colleague David Ornstein and the Mail‘ Lewis Steele among those to note Diomande as one of the primary candidates to succeed Salah.

However Leipzig’s price tag, currently set at €100 million (£86.6m), is described as “excessive” and could prove an obvious issue in any pursuit.

Nevertheless Diomande is seen as a player who “fits the club’s profile” and a move cannot be ruled out at this stage – particularly as his asking price may drop.



