As reported by talkSPORT‘s Alex Crook last month, if Leipzig fail to qualify for next season’s Champions League their resolve over a deal for the No. 49 could be tested.

Leipzig are currently fourth in the Bundesliga which would be enough to secure a place among Europe’s elite, but they are locked in a battle with Stuttgart, Hoffenheim and Bayer Leverkusen for two spots in the top four.